              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17371689-kimberly?shelf=group-read">group-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17371689-kimberly?shelf=supernatural">supernatural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17371689-kimberly?shelf=literary">literary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17371689-kimberly?shelf=public-domain">public-domain</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer727714752" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6250568682828435656"><b>GHOST STORIES OF AN ANTIQUARY</b>, contains some of the earlier tales of author M.R. James. This particular selection is available for free download on public domain.<br/><br/>I&apos;ll admit, I&apos;m a bit biased when it comes to M.R. James&apos; tales--I own his complete works, and have re-read it several times. While this collection doesn&apos;t include all of his better known stories, it does give the reader a good sampling of that eerie, creeping horror--usually without all the gore--that James is better known for. These a</span>
  <span id="freeText6250568682828435656" style="display:none"><b>GHOST STORIES OF AN ANTIQUARY</b>, contains some of the earlier tales of author M.R. James. This particular selection is available for free download on public domain.<br /><br />I'll admit, I'm a bit biased when it comes to M.R. James' tales--I own his complete works, and have re-read it several times. While this collection doesn't include all of his better known stories, it does give the reader a good sampling of that eerie, creeping horror--usually without all the gore--that James is better known for. These are the kind of stories that affect you more, in my humble opinion, and often the ones that you don't forget over time.<br /><br />A great start to some of M.R. James' work.<br /><br />Highly recommended!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6250568682828435656" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
