<div id="review_183323950" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/183323950" />
    <a title="Tania Donald" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5764712-tania-donald"><img alt="Tania Donald" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1357014021p2/5764712.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/183323950?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tania Donald" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tania Donald" href="/user/show/5764712-tania-donald">Tania Donald</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer183323950" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16374869188610790296">As Leonardo is to painting, so M R James is to the short ghost story. He really is that good. These stories are like beautifully crafted little gems, rich in tiny, exquisite detail, and sparkling with dark beauty.<br/>There is an indefinable rare something that marks out the greatest writers of supernatural fiction. H P Lovecraft had it, and M R James had it. It&apos;s a kind of mood, an atmosphere, but it&apos;s more than that. Effortlessly, these writers draw you into a world where the most strange and terri</span>
  <span id="freeText16374869188610790296" style="display:none">As Leonardo is to painting, so M R James is to the short ghost story. He really is that good. These stories are like beautifully crafted little gems, rich in tiny, exquisite detail, and sparkling with dark beauty.<br />There is an indefinable rare something that marks out the greatest writers of supernatural fiction. H P Lovecraft had it, and M R James had it. It's a kind of mood, an atmosphere, but it's more than that. Effortlessly, these writers draw you into a world where the most strange and terrible things are entirely plausible; plausible, horrifying and delicious.<br />My words can't do justice to M R James. I can only urge you, if you are someone who enjoys tales of the supernatural, to read any of his stories that you can get your hands on. <br />(There is also a very fine audio-book of this available to download for free at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.librivox.org">www.librivox.org</a>)</span>
  <a data-text-id="16374869188610790296" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


